      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAY STREET (3) started favourite and led for the judge but was given windburn by Journeyman first-up over this distance at Warwick Farm. Unlikely to encounter one that smart today and with the run under the belt he is a big chance to open his account. PELEUS (6) settled well back then sprouted wings late but just missed when resuming over 1000m at Gosford last time out. An extra 200m on this bigger track is ideal. Looks a different proposition since being gelded and can give the top pick a run for his money. MAIDOFF (4) recovered from a slow start to get up for third recently over 1100m at Wyong. Better placed under this scenario and he should prove tough to hold out. The speedy WAN LOST (1) just failed to hang on over today's journey at Gosford last start. Progressing nicely and won't spend a penny from gate one. BRICKOWSKI (2) is a first starter by Ole Kirk from stakes winner Steps In Time who has thrown six winners from six foals. Recent trial winner who is ready to run.",
